article.headline: Milwaukee 81, Green Bay 75
article.story: GREEN BAY, Wis. -- Paris Gulley hit six 3-pointers, scoring 20 points, and Milwaukee beat Green Bay 81-75 on Saturday. Kaylon Williams had 16 points and eight assists, Kyle Kelm had 14 points and James Haarsma scored 11 for Milwaukee, which led most of the way though never by more than 10 points. The Panthers (15-10, 8-5 Horizon) were 12 for 23 from 3-point range, with Gulley missing only once from beyond the arc and seven players connecting on at least one 3-pointer. Keifer Sykes led the Phoenix (9-13, 5-7) with 25 points. Alec Brown had 18 points and 10 rebounds for Green Bay, and Kam Cerroni added 17 points. Both teams had 27 field goals, but the Phoenix only had four 3-pointers.
